WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.780
E ora è un onore, a seconda della gente del Protectorate di Albania,

00:07.000 --> 00:12.160
di dare la piazza all'italiano prime ministero e protettore del nostro paese, Giorgio Melone.

00:16.540 --> 00:17.720
Buongiorno a tutti, amici.

00:20.540 --> 00:24.540
Mi chiedo di dire grazie a Eddie, non per essere un protectorate,

00:24.840 --> 00:29.140
ma per la sua ospitalità calda e il suo sommet.

00:29.140 --> 00:38.400
E anche per farmi sentire molto giovane di nuovo con quel video che ha mostrato in l'inaugurazione.

00:39.920 --> 00:47.320
E voglio anche congratulare Eddie per la sua reelezione assolutamente inespettata

00:48.100 --> 00:52.040
come leader del governo albanese.

00:53.000 --> 00:59.880
Sono felice che l'Europa continui a raccontare il suo spirito e la sua determinazione.

01:00.420 --> 01:03.700
Albania chiede alla comunità politica europea per la prima volta,

01:04.220 --> 01:13.700
la valgo particolarmente significativa, non solo per questa nazione, ma per tutti noi.

01:14.650 --> 01:19.880
Ho sempre considerato l'identità europea come un fattore,

01:20.200 --> 01:23.960
fondamentale dalla storia, anche prima della geografia.

01:24.140 --> 01:31.460
Un concetto che è più difficile di incontrare in una definizione che di capire con l'impulso.

01:32.200 --> 01:38.900
Albania è ovviamente l'Europa, come l'Italia, la Serbia o la Norvega,

01:38.900 --> 01:44.200
non importa se sono parte di questa o quella organizzazione.

01:44.500 --> 01:50.340
Questo è il motivo per cui sono sempre felice quando qualcuno tenta di raccogliere il diritto

01:50.340 --> 01:52.800
per decidere chi è l'Europa e chi non è.

01:53.180 --> 02:00.980
Tra gli Stati che sono qui oggi, alcuni hanno deciso di non ingiuntare all'Europa,

02:01.640 --> 02:03.260
altri sono ispirati a essere parte.

02:03.260 --> 02:06.460
Inoltre, i Stati che sono qui oggi sono più o meno europei,

02:09.680 --> 02:14.740
ma l'Europa è oggi la casa di Sandro Comandante,

02:14.740 --> 02:19.000
per raggiungere il riuscito di unificatione europea,

02:19.860 --> 02:23.500
attenzione ai mongoli, a persone che possono differenziare tra l'altro,

02:24.060 --> 02:29.000
ma sono parte di un'altra, come le mani diverse di una mano.

02:29.800 --> 02:37.860
Le persone che hanno battuto oltre i secoli sono in realtà una sola persona.

02:38.860 --> 02:43.500
Inoltre, per questo motivo, sono qui oggi per fare un passo avanti

02:43.500 --> 02:45.820
nel processo storico di unificare l'Europa,

02:45.840 --> 02:49.660
perché se vogliamo costruire una nuova Europa in un nuovo mondo,

02:50.440 --> 02:53.320
non possiamo immaginare di farlo senza i balcani stessi,

02:53.960 --> 02:57.240
senza le loro persone, senza le loro identità e le loro background storiche.

02:58.120 --> 03:04.620
I balcani stessi non sovrapponono il finger dell'Europa o del nostro continente.

03:04.620 --> 03:07.820
Siamo al very heart del nostro continente.

03:08.200 --> 03:10.500
Siamo la regione bridge tra l'est e l'est,

03:10.720 --> 03:16.740
tra quello che St. John Paul II ha voluto chiamare i due lunghi d'Europa.

03:17.740 --> 03:20.580
Per questo motivo, l'Italia è committa in Brasile

03:20.580 --> 03:23.840
a servire un approccio strategico per i balcani stessi

03:23.840 --> 03:29.060
per prendere into due account despite the complex challenges posed by the region.

03:30.260 --> 03:34.740
They need to provide these countries with a clear EU integration perspective.

03:35.740 --> 03:38.340
Of course, enlargement involves new challenges,

03:38.440 --> 03:41.740
but I am convinced that the European integration of Western Balkans

03:41.740 --> 03:48.020
as well as towards the East is also strategic investment on Europe's own security,

03:48.600 --> 03:53.200
even more so in light of what is happening on our borders.

03:53.840 --> 03:58.140
We live in an extremely interconnected world.

03:58.940 --> 04:02.560
Our destiny is interdependence is fact.

04:03.280 --> 04:06.040
What happens on European's eastern borders

04:06.600 --> 04:12.860
is connected with what happens on its Mediterranean borders and vice versa.

04:14.260 --> 04:19.280
The wound that Russia's wars of aggression against Ukraine has inflicted

04:20.120 --> 04:25.800
on the rules-based international system still produces the stabilizing effects

04:26.420 --> 04:31.540
well beyond the war borders and, like a domino,

04:32.240 --> 04:39.120
this contributes to reigniting or detonating other crisis hotbeds, crisis hotbeds.

04:39.700 --> 04:44.020
We have witnessed this in the Middle East and not only there.

04:45.020 --> 04:47.880
That is why we will continue to stand by Ukraine

04:48.440 --> 04:52.940
and to strive for this war to immediately come to an end

04:52.940 --> 04:58.400
because our security and freedom depend on restoring the force of law

04:58.400 --> 05:00.860
over the law of the strongest.

05:01.880 --> 05:04.240
And speaking of Europe and freedom,

05:05.400 --> 05:09.780
I believe it is nothing more European than a people willing to risk everything

05:09.780 --> 05:12.260
to defend its own freedom and independence.

05:13.560 --> 05:17.860
Every day the heroism and tenacity of the Ukrainian people reminds us

05:18.740 --> 05:24.260
what Europe is and what the deepest aspect of our common identity is, freedom.

05:25.400 --> 05:27.320
We defend our freedom and we want peace.

05:27.580 --> 05:34.360
Volodymyr and the Ukrainian people want peace and we newly witnessed it yesterday.

05:35.240 --> 05:43.280
The world saw who was really willing to sit at a negotiation table and who was not.

05:44.080 --> 05:47.120
And this shows also with respect to certain propaganda

05:47.880 --> 05:50.200
who looks for peace and who doesn't.

05:51.300 --> 05:55.880
At the same time we must not interpret what happened yesterday as a setback

05:56.520 --> 05:58.160
and throw in the towel.

05:58.260 --> 06:02.020
Instead we must insist with determination to finally achieve

06:03.020 --> 06:06.700
an unconditioned ceasefire and a true peace agreement

06:06.700 --> 06:10.980
with serious security guarantees for Ukraine

06:10.980 --> 06:14.500
and we are absolutely ready to do what is needed to reach this goal.

06:15.540 --> 06:21.540
However, colleagues, I do agree with many things that Eddie said in his speech,

06:22.920 --> 06:28.120
but building a new Europe in a new world as advocated by this session means,

06:28.200 --> 06:33.900
in my opinion, before talking about what we have to do,

06:34.400 --> 06:42.040
starting from our very foundations and reflecting mainly on who we are.

06:42.600 --> 06:48.260
None of us is interested in strengthening any form of union amongst European states,

06:49.360 --> 06:54.140
if not for protecting what we are and what we want to continue to be in the coming decades

06:54.140 --> 06:57.600
and centuries in such a fast-changing world.

06:58.660 --> 07:02.940
Because if Europe sometimes proves unable to face the great challenges,

07:03.700 --> 07:06.100
it is no one else's fault.

07:06.660 --> 07:08.560
It is our responsibility.

07:09.780 --> 07:16.280
And it is up to us to choose whether to go along a decline or instead fight it.

07:17.300 --> 07:21.040
And if we decide to fight it, first of all, we need to regain awareness,

07:21.920 --> 07:26.080
which is mainly awareness of who we are, what the European civilization is,

07:26.660 --> 07:31.600
of the great achievements it has accomplished across the history of humankind.

07:32.560 --> 07:38.040
A synthesis of values resulting from the encounter between Greek philosophy,

07:38.040 --> 07:44.480
Roman law, Christian humanism, a synthesis of values that allow the European civilization

07:44.480 --> 07:49.780
to conceive a world in which the person's central life is sacred and human beings are free

07:49.780 --> 07:50.780
and equal.

07:51.460 --> 07:56.580
A civilization that respects the identities of the others without denying its own

07:56.580 --> 08:01.280
and that builds peace where instead others see destruction.

08:01.600 --> 08:02.600
We are this.

08:03.500 --> 08:05.180
We are this before everything.

08:05.980 --> 08:09.340
And I think we have, first of all, to remember it every day

08:09.340 --> 08:12.540
if we want to build a Europe up to the role received from history.

08:12.760 --> 08:13.100
Thank you.

